c bus\",\n","      p_nom=10,\n","      marginal_cost=german_prices_2025)\n","\n","# Verify the time-varying marginal cost was added correctly\n","print(\"Network snapshots:\", len(network_El.snapshots))\n","print(\"\\nMarginal Cost Profile (First 5 hours):\")\n","print(network_El.generators_t.marginal_cost.head())"],"metadata":{"id":"tX-FAQ2TEccD","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774270489683,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":87,"user":{"displayName":"Igor Kovacevic","userId":"01095176641533826550"}},"outputId":"e0aa292b-c6cd-47d0-97e8-0890aebec207"},"execution_count":18,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Network snapshots: 24\n","\n","Marginal Cost Profile (First 5 hours):\n","name                 Grid Import\n","snapshot                        \n","2025-01-01 00:00:00         65.0\n","2025-01-01 01:00:00         62.0\n","2025-01-01 02:00:00         60.0\n","2025-01-01 03:00:00         62.0\n","2025-01-01 04:00:00         68.0\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"2f8f8431","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":507},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774270489916,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":222,"user":{"displayName":"Igor Kovacevic","userId":"01095176641533826550"}},"outputId":"00236496-c14f-42a1-910d-0348c4abcf8f"},"source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# Extract the marginal cost for the Grid Import generator\n","marginal_costs = network_El.generators_t.marginal_cost[\"Grid Import\"]\n","\n","# Plotting\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n","plt.step(network_El.snapshots, marginal_costs, linestyle='-', where='post')\n","plt.title(\"Hourly Marginal Costs for Grid Import\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Time\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Marginal Cost (€/MWh)\")\n","plt.grid(True)\n","plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"execution_count":19,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Storage and Demand H2"],"metadata":{"id":"G61p_banLEsJ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# 2. Add a 'Store' component named \"Hydrogen Tank\"\n","# e_nom=70 means it can store 70 MWh of Hydrogen energy\n","network_El.add(\"Store\", \"Hydrogen Tank\",\n","            bus=\"Hydrogen bus\",\n","            e_nom=100)\n","\n","# 3. Create a list for the load profile\n","# 0 MW for the first 23 hours, 50 MW for the last hour\n","target_load_profile = [0] * 23 + [50]\n","\n","# 4. Add a new 'Load' component named \"Target Load\"\n","# We check if it exists first to avoid errors if this cell is re-run\n","if \"Target Load\" in network_El.loads.index:\n","    # If it exists, we might want to update it, but for simplicity here we just print or remove/re-add\n","    network_El.remove(\"Load\", \"Target Load\")\n","\n","network_El.add(\"Load\", \"Target Load\",\n","            bus=\"Hydrogen bus\",\n","            p_set=target_load_profile)\n","\n","print(\"Added 'Hydrogen Tank' and 'Target Load'.\")"],"metadata":{"id":"gv3qpRUAKE8V","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774270489921,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":6,"user":{"displayName":"Igor Kovacevic","userId":"01095176641533826550"}},"outputId":"822ac6d3-9ff1-4e6a-c774-fba40b43956d"},"execution_count":20,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Added 'Hydrogen Tank' and 'Target Load'.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Electrolyzers Models"],"metadata":{"id":"HBeocKC7G3qU"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# =========================================================\n","# LAYER 3: Dynamic Inertia with Shut-Down Ramp Limits\n","# =========================================================\n","case = 2\n","\n","if \"Electrolyzer\" in network_El.links.index:\n","  network_El.remove(\"Link\", \"Electrolyzer\")\n","\n","# simplest eletrolyzer model\n","if case == 1:\n","  network_El.add(\"Link\", \"Electrolyzer\",\n","    bus0=\"Electric bus\",\n","    bus1=\"Hydrogen bus\",\n","    p_nom=10,\n","    efficiency=0.70)\n","\n","# electrolyzer model with minimum run\n","if case == 2:\n","  network_El.add(\"Link\", \"Electrolyzer\",\n","    bus0=\"Electric bus\",\n","    bus1=\"Hydrogen bus\",\n","    p_nom=10,\n","    efficiency=0.70,\n","    committable=True,     # Enables binary On/Off logic\n","    p_min_pu=0.20)        # Must run at >= 2 MW, or be exactly 0 MW\n","\n","# electrolyzer with ramp_up and ramp_down introduction\n","if case == 3:\n","  network_El.add(\"Link\", \"Electrolyzer\",\n","    bus0=\"Electric bus\",\n","    bus1=\"Hydrogen bus\",\n","    p_nom=10,\n","    efficiency=0.70,\n","    committable=True,\n","    ramp_limit_up=0.25,   # Max 20% increase per hour\n","    ramp_limit_down=0.25, # Max 20% decrease while staying ON\n","    ramp_limit_shut_down=0.25, # Forces gradual ramp even when turning OFF\n","    start_up_cost=500,\n","    min_up_time=4)\n","\n","# model with introduction of various buses - electricity, hydrogen, water and heat\n","if case == 5:\n","  network_El.add(\"Link\", \"Electrolyzer\",\n","    bus0=\"Electric bus\",      # Power input\n","    bus1=\"Hydrogen bus\",      # H2 output\n","    bus2=\"Water bus\",         # Water input\n","    bus3=\"Heat bus\",          # Heat output\n","    p_nom=10,\n","\n","    # The Mass and Thermal Balance\n","    efficiency=0.70,          # Yields 70% H2\n","    efficiency2=-0.189,       # Consumes ~0.189 tons H2O per MWh of electricity\n","    efficiency3=0.20,         # Outputs 20% of energy as low-T waste heat\n","    committable=True,\n","    ramp_limit_up=0.25,   # Max 20% increase per hour\n","    ramp_limit_down=0.25, # Max 20% decrease while staying ON\n","    ramp_limit_shut_down=0.25, # Forces gradual ramp even when turning OFF\n","    start_up_cost=500,\n","    min_up_time=4)\n"],"metadata":{"id":"KOstdFHiZMJx","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774270763837,"user